entry.def: Take-up is the rate at which people apply for or buy something which is offered, for example financial help from the government or shares in a company.

example.ex: ...a major campaign to increase the take-up of welfare benefits.
example.tran: 一场声势浩大的旨在增加福利待遇申请、接受率的运动
